 Biose Tools People Publications Courses Cooperation Contact Us BIOSE BIOSE - Biological System Engineering Group is part of the Biochemical Engineering Department at Federal University of Rio de Janeiro. It was dedicated to deal with different aspects related to Microbiology, Biochemical Kinetics, Modeling and Optimization that leads to productivity enhancement in bioprocesses. The main areas developed in BIOSE research activities drive us through: Cell stress responses Digital image analysis applied to biological systems Enzymatic technology in petroleum off-shore exploration Enzyme production in multiphase systems Glycerol Biovalorization Novel solvents (fluorinated compounds and ionic liquids) in biological systems Valorization of Amazon products through biomass enzymatic treatment http://www.eq.ufrj.br/biose/index.html 
